text: <@U7SL518D6> HubSpot form is throwing this error on the console and as a result the email validation is giving a false response of not valid yet it is valid

Hi all,

I have a quote calculator. Where I am populating HubSpot fields with my calculated values.

When I set the value of each field with javascript it appears to be functioning fine. However upon submission my populated field values aren't being submitted and go through as blank.

I am using the form field rather than the JS embed code, however I don't think this would be the reason for this not working. I have checked the values on submission of the form and they come back as empty.
